article.headline: Dartmouth 64, Maryland-Eastern Shore 59
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- In his first game back from a broken hand, reserve Dan Biber scored 14 points to lead Dartmouth past Maryland-Eastern Shore 64-59 on Saturday. Biber had missed the previous seven games with the injury, which he suffered during the third game of the season. Elgin Fitzgerald added 12 points on 6-of-7 shooting for the Big Green (4-7), and Michael Giovacchini also scored 12 -- including six during a crucial stretch in the second half. The Hawks (2-10) had four players in double figures. Corey Brown scored 18 points, Jesse Brooks had 14, Antonio McMillion added 13 and Ed Tyson finished with 10. McMillion also had 12 rebounds. Dartmouth led 32-28 at halftime, but UMES rallied to take a 55-50 lead with 4:17 left in the game. Giovacchini scored six straight points to give the Big Green a 56-55 lead with 2:57 to play, and Alex Barnett and Biber hit jumpers to extend the lead to 60-57 with less than a minute left. Giovacchini and Biber each made a pair of free throws with less than 15 seconds remaining to put the game out of reach.
